3. Iterators

🛠️ Objects to traverse containers (like smart pointers).

Types:

Input Iterator → istream_iterator

Output Iterator → ostream_iterator

Forward Iterator → works forward only

Bidirectional Iterator → works forward & backward (list, set, map)

Random Access Iterator → allows +,-,<,> (vector, deque, array)

Important Functions:

begin(), end()

rbegin(), rend()

advance(it, n) → moves iterator n steps

next(it) / prev(it)

📌 DSA Priority Order

begin(), end()

auto (range-based for loops)

next(), prev(), advance()

rbegin(), rend()